Diagram 4 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par By now, you must think something is strange. Yes, it is. You cannot capture black by playing inside.
\par
\par White 1 is a brilliant move to narrow down black's eyespace.  Now that this move is played, black has no way to live.
\par
\par If black plays at 2, white plays at 3 and 5 and that's it. It's not pik. If the outside liberties are filled in, black's whole group is in dansu. Black is dead!
\par
\par Please check for yourself.
\par }
